"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758040","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>Housing Associations do not meet the conditions for inclusion within Schedule 1 of the FOI Act. However the Government keeps the scope of the Act under constant review.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758040/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:25:36.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758040/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758040/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-06","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will make an assessment of the merits of including housing associations in the list of bodies subject to freedom of information requests in response to the Grenfell Tower tragedy.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","9122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758041","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The rules for boundary Reviews are set out in the Parliamentary Constituencies Act 1986, as amended by the Parliamentary Voting System and Constituencies Act 2011.</p><p> </p><p>The rules stipulate that the number of constituencies is 600 and that all constituencies, subject to a limited number of exceptions, must be between 95% and 105% of the United Kingdom electoral quota, which is the average number of electors per constituency. Reviews are to be conducted every five years.</p><p>The rules are designed to ensure that there is fairness in the setting of parliamentary constituencies and having seats of an equal size will ensure everyone’s vote will carry equal weight.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","9111","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758041/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-12T09:30:37.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758041/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758041/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-06","Constituencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what model the Boundary Commission will employ in its new review of constituency boundaries.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","9109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758042","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The rules for boundary Reviews are set out in the Parliamentary Constituencies Act 1986, as amended by the Parliamentary Voting System and Constituencies Act 2011.</p><p> </p><p>The rules stipulate that the number of constituencies is 600 and that all constituencies, subject to a limited number of exceptions, must be between 95% and 105% of the United Kingdom electoral quota, which is the average number of electors per constituency. Reviews are to be conducted every five years.</p><p>The rules are designed to ensure that there is fairness in the setting of parliamentary constituencies and having seats of an equal size will ensure everyone’s vote will carry equal weight.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","9109","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758042/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-12T09:30:37.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758042/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758042/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-06","Constituencies: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what model the Boundary Commission will employ in its new review of constituency boundaries in Wales.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","9111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758043","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>It is my intention to reconvene the Joint Ministerial Committee (EU Negotiations) in the autumn and we are working with the devolved administrations to secure a date in October. The UK Government is committed to consultation with the devolved administrations, both within the formal structures of the Joint Ministerial Committee and also through bilateral discussions.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758043/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T14:28:52.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758043/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758043/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-06","Joint Ministerial Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to his oral contribution of 5 September 2016, Official Report, column 65, when the Joint Ministerial Committee will next meet.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","9054"
