"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758067","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","The Government has previously consulted extensively on the impacts of abolishing Class 2 NICs and responded to this consultation at Autumn Statement. This response is available at https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/consultation-on-abolishing-class-2-national-insurance-and-introducing-a-contributory-benefit-test-to-class-4-national-insurance-for-the-self-employed. The Government published a tax information and impact note on this policy at Autumn Statement 2016. The figures requested are not available.<p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","9080 ; 9081 ; 9098","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758067/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:03:25.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758067/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758067/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-06","National Insurance Contributions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of granting people earning less than £6,000 a year the same pension rights that come with Class 4 contributions after the abolition of the Class 2 bracket.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","9097"
