"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758085","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-11","<p>In 2016-17 we offered local authorities a 4-year settlement through to 2020. This offer was accepted by 97 per cent of councils. Further support would be considered as part of a spending review.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758085/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:03:26.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758085/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758085/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Revenue Support Grant","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether it remains his policy to phase out the revenue support grant by 2020.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","9116"
