"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758090","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-25","<p>We want to explore how local authorities can build high quality sustainable communities. We are looking to strike housing deals with councils to support ambitious and innovative plans for additional homes in high demand areas, including pro-development councils that wish to build more council housing. We are making good progress and will announce further details in due course.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","9143","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758090/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-25T11:15:58.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758090/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758090/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has for new council housing deals with local authorities to provide more social housing.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9142"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758091","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-25","<p>We want to explore how local authorities can build high quality sustainable communities. We are looking to strike housing deals with councils to support ambitious and innovative plans for additional homes in high demand areas, including pro-development councils that wish to build more council housing. We are making good progress and will announce further details in due course.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","9142","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758091/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-25T11:15:58.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758091/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758091/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has put in place to encourage local councils to build new fixed-term social houses with an automatic right-to-buy.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758092","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Government will set out its plans for a review of business rates in due course.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758092/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:04:06.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758092/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758092/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to conduct a full review of the business rates system.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","9030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758093","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-25","<p>The Government has made no such estimates. It is the responsibility of local authorities to assess all local housing needs through their local plan.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758093/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-25T11:34:32.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758093/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758093/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he makes of the adequacy of the number of transit pitches made available to Travellers in (a) England and (b) South Gloucestershire.","false","Biography information for Jack Lopresti","Filton and Bradley Stoke","Jack Lopresti","8996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758094","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department does not hold information about the number of properties in receipt of transitional relief.</p><p>A £3.6 billion transitional relief scheme is providing support for the minority of businesses who face increases at the 2017 revaluation. Transitional relief is applied automatically to bills by local authorities.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758094/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:04:37.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758094/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758094/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many and what proportion of businesses eligible for business rates transitional relief have received that relief in the last 12 months for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","9016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758095","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-15","<p>The Department currently offers the service for the public to request information and correspondence in British Sign Language (BSL), through our print supplier.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758095/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T12:59:44.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758095/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758095/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Department for Communities and Local Government: Sign Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department takes to provide (a) information on its services in British Sign Language (BSL) and (b) correspondence in BSL to people whose principal language is BSL.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","9000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758096","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-25","<p>The £2.3 billion Housing Infrastructure Fund, launched on 4 July 2017, will unlock up to 100,000 new homes by supporting the delivery of vital physical infrastructure projects such as roads, bridges, energy networks and other utilities. Local authorities have been invited to submit bids by 28 September and decisions about funding will be taken after this date.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758096/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-25T11:23:37.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758096/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758096/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Housing Infrastructure Fund: Barnet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much has been received by the London Borough of Barnet from the Housing Infrastructure Fund; and which projects have been so funded.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","9210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758097","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>Details of each local authority’s Discretionary Housing Payment funding and expenditure are published for each financial year and can be found on the GOV.UK website at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/discretionary-housing-payments-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/discretionary-housing-payments-statistics</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758097/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T11:55:41.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758097/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758097/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-06","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much each local authority was allocated in Discretionary Housing Payment funding in each of the last three years; and how much each authority has spent from that funding in each such year.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","9287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758098","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>Discretionary Housing Payments are specifically used for the purpose of helping individuals with their housing costs provided they are in receipt of either Housing Benefit or the housing costs element of Universal Credit.</p><p> </p><p>These payments are very flexible and can be considered where, in the local authority’s opinion, further financial assistance towards housing costs is required. Local Authorities are able to set their own policy, criteria and application process with payments being made entirely at their discretion.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","9286","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758098/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T12:03:20.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758098/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758098/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-06","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that Discretionary Housing Payments are being spent for the intended purpose by local authorities.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","9288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758099","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-20","<p>I have met with representatives of national tenant organisations to seek their views on this process and a programme of events is currently been drawn up so I can personally meet and hear from as many social tenants both in the immediate area around Grenfell Tower but also across the country.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758099/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-20T12:57:02.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758099/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758099/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Grenfell Tower Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the Prime Minister's letter relating to the Grenfell Tower Inquiry of 15 August 2017 to the right hon. Sir Martin Moore-Bick, how much time has been allocated for the Housing Minister to meet and hear from as many social housing tenants as possible; how long that exercise will last for; and how findings from that exercise will be reported.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758100","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-11","<p>Our priority is to get everyone from Grenfell Tower and Grenfell Walk whose homes were lost in the fire permanently rehoused as soon as possible. But it's important to get this right and ensure residents have choice over their housing options.</p><p>My Rt Hon Friend, the Secretary of State, reported on recent progress in his statement to the House on 5 September.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758100/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T14:54:41.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758100/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758100/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent progress has been made on rehousing survivors of the Grenfell Tower fire.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","9297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758101","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-05","<p>The Government has made no such estimates. It is the responsibility of local authorities to assess all local housing needs through their local plan.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","9131 ; 9188 ; 9189","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758101/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-05T15:49:05.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758101/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758101/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to his Department's August 2015 Planning Policy for Traveller Sites (PPTS), how many local planning authorities have set pitch targets for Gypsies and Travellers using the revised definition as set out in Annex 1 of the PPTS 2015.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","9187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758102","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-05","<p>The Government has made no such estimates. It is the responsibility of local authorities to assess all local housing needs through their local plan.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","9131 ; 9187 ; 9189","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758102/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-05T15:49:05.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758102/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758102/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many Travellers who conform to the revised definition of Gypsy Travellers as set out in the Planning Policy for Traveller Sites 2015 have been successful in obtaining a pitch in the last year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","9188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758103","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-05","<p>The Government has made no such estimates. It is the responsibility of local authorities to assess all local housing needs through their local plan.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","9131 ; 9187 ; 9188","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758103/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-05T15:49:05.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758103/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758103/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many and which local authorities have met the requirement (a) in the Planning Policy for Traveller Sites 2015 to identify and maintain a supply of specific deliverable sites, sufficient to provide five years' worth of sites, against their locally set target and (b) to include the same outcome for each of the next five, six and 10 years as set down in the Planning Policy for Travellers Sites document.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","9189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758104","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-14","<p>In December 2016 the Prime Minister and the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government announced support for 84 projects through our £50 million Homelessness Prevention Programme, to deliver an end-to-end approach to homelessness prevention, which included £30 million for Rough Sleepers. A number of these areas are already using the Housing First model as part of their approach.</p><p>We are also aiming to halve rough sleeping by 2022 and eliminate it altogether by 2027. To achieve this we are setting up a rough sleeping and homelessness taskforce and piloting a Housing First approach on a larger scale to tackle rough sleeping. We will announce further details shortly.</p><p>This should be a country that works for everyone, especially the most vulnerable in society, and we are committed to making sure everyone has a roof over their heads.</p><p><br></p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758104/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T16:02:51.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758104/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758104/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the announcement made by him and the Prime Minister on 21 December 2016, on tackling homelessness, when he expects the trials of the Housing First model to begin.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758105","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>Discretionary Housing Payments are specifically used for the purpose of helping individuals with their housing costs provided they are in receipt of either Housing Benefit or the housing costs element of Universal Credit.</p><p> </p><p>These payments are very flexible and can be considered where, in the local authority’s opinion, further financial assistance towards housing costs is required. Local Authorities are able to set their own policy, criteria and application process with payments being made entirely at their discretion.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","9288","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758105/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T12:03:20.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758105/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758105/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-06","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that people who want to access Discretionary Housing Payments are not blocked by overly strict criteria set by local authorities.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","9286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758106","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-20","<p>We plan to publish the Draft Tenants Fees Bill shortly.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758106/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-20T13:06:43.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758106/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758106/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Letting Agents: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to publish the Draft Tenants Fees Bill.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758107","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-20","<p>On 5 September 2017, we published consolidated advice for building owners following large-scale testing which can be viewed here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/building-safety-programme-update-and-consolidated-advice-for-building-owners-following-large-scale-testing" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/building-safety-programme-update-and-consolidated-advice-for-building-owners-following-large-scale-testing</a></p><p>The results include private accommodation in two categories: private residential and private student residential.</p><p>The Secretary of State has urged all private owners of similar blocks to submit samples of cladding for testing. He has also asked local authorities to ensure that residents of private sector buildings are safe and has asked them to collect the data on these buildings so that we have a complete picture of the private sector.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758107/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-20T13:08:20.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758107/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758107/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of private high-rise residential blocks that have one of the four types of cladding and insulation combinations assessed as non-compliant with building regulations guidance BR135 by local authority area.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758108","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-05","<p>As set out in consolidated advice to building owners published on 5 September, the government is working with the Expert Panel to consider whether there are any heightened risks linked to other cladding systems (not Aluminium Composite Material) and broader fire and building safety issues in high-rise buildings.</p><p>As a first step to understand what other cladding systems may be safe on high rise buildings, the Building Research Establishment (BRE) has sought permission from its clients and is publishing a list of historical data on cladding systems which have passed the BS8414 test set out in current Building Regulations guidance. The catalogue can be accessed here <a href="https://www.bre.co.uk/regulatory-testing" target="_blank">https://www.bre.co.uk/regulatory-testing</a>.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758108/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-05T15:44:36.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758108/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758108/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to ensure that high-rise residential accommodation with external cladding that is not composed of aluminium composite material is tested to ensure that it is fire safe.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758109","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-05","<p>The Council are working to provide a new home in social housing for all former residents of Grenfell Tower and Grenfell Walk within one year, while giving households the time and space to make this transition at their own pace.</p><p>The Council published the rehousing commitment to residents on 21 July and is available at: <a href="https://www.rbkc.gov.uk/sites/default/files/atoms/files/The%20housing%20commitment%20to%20residents%20%E2%80%93%20FAQ.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.rbkc.gov.uk/sites/default/files/atoms/files/The%20housing%20commitment%20to%20residents%20%E2%80%93%20FAQ.pdf</a></p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758109/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-05T16:04:24.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758109/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758109/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, by what date he plans that all the households eligible for rehousing as a result of the Grenfell Tower fire will receive an offer of permanent housing.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758110","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-20","<p>Following the completion of the large-scale system tests, we have published consolidated advice to building owners which contains a summary of the numbers of initial screening tests which have been completed to date by the Building Research Establishment:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/building-safety-programme-update-and-consolidated-advice-for-building-owners-following-large-scale-testing" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/building-safety-programme-update-and-consolidated-advice-for-building-owners-following-large-scale-testing</a></p><p>Where social housing buildings fail the tests, local authorities in England are informing the relevant constituency MP.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758110/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-20T13:01:40.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758110/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758110/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many social housing blocks have failed the recent fire safety tests co-ordinated by his Department in each local authority area.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758111","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-11","<p>As we confirmed in our letter to local authorities on 31 July, the Government is willing to consider the removal of financial restrictions to enable local authorities to fund essential fire safety works.</p><p>If a housing association has concerns about its ability to meet the cost of essential works, it must contact the Social Housing Regulator. The Regulator has written to housing associations to reiterate this message.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758111/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T14:50:51.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758111/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758111/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much funding his Department has set aside for remedial work in response to the Grenfell Tower fire; and whether such funding is additional to existing departmental allocations.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","9295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758112","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-09-15","<p>We endeavour to communicate in the best way for our audiences and aim to meet specific communication or access to information requirements as requested or when a specific need has been identified.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758112/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T09:26:00.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758112/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758112/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-09-06","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Sign Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps her Department takes to provide (a) information on its services in British Sign Language (BSL) and (b) correspondence in BSL to people whose principal language is BSL.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","9001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758113","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-09-12","<p>I have regular discussions with the English Football League and the FA on a number of matters. I am aware that talks around where the club will be playing its home matches from next season are still ongoing. I would urge all relevant parties to agree a plan, so that attention can turn to working together, to provide the clarity needed for the club and its loyal supporters.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758113/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-12T16:51:01.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758113/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758113/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-09-06","Coventry City Football Club: Sportsgrounds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether she has had recent discussions with the (a) English Football League or (b) Football Association on Coventry City Football Club's search for a long-term stadium solution within Coventry.","false","Biography information for Colleen Fletcher","Coventry North East","Colleen Fletcher","9077"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758114","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-09-14","<p>I have met with the Fundraising Regulator to discuss a range of matters regarding charity fundraising.</p><p> </p><p>The Fundraising Regulator has updated the Code of Fundraising Practice in relation to house to house collections of goods. From 30 September 2017 charities must not deliver bags to properties that display a notice clearly indicating that the householder does not wish to donate through this method.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758114/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T14:31:35.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758114/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758114/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-09-06","Charitable Donations: Plastic Bags","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with the charity sector on the practice of posting plastic bags through people's letterboxes.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","9110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758115","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-09-14","<p>DCMS has received services from the Behavioural Insights Team since 2014. This has enabled the department to add to its evidence base to support priority government areas.</p><p> </p><p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p> </p><p>https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive</p><p> </p><p>Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p>https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","9676","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758115/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T16:42:58.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758115/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758115/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-09-06","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Behavioural Insights Team","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how much her Department paid to the Behavioural Insights Team in each year since 2014.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","9183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758116","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-15","<p>The Ministry of Defence has received services from the Behavioural Insights Team since 2014. This has enabled the Department to add to its evidence base to support priority Government areas.</p><p>Since January 2011, details of central Government contracts above the value of £10,000 have been published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive. Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","9962","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758116/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T13:26:29.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758116/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758116/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-06","Ministry of Defence: Behavioural Insights Team","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department paid to the Behavioural Insights Team in each year since 2014.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","9184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758117","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-14","<p>Expert analysts examine data from every UK strike to assess its effect with one of their priorities being to highlight any possible indications of civilian casualties or collateral damage. Information on potential civilian casualties reported to the Ministry of Defence by external parties is also assessed by the Department. The number of staff involved will vary depending on the circumstances of each case. The costs to the Department are not recorded separately.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758117/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:25:26.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758117/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758117/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-06","Islamic State: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much UK (a) funding, (b) personnel and (c) other resources have been used for civilian harm tracking as part of Operation Inherent Resolve.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","9247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758118","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-14","<p>It is long standing policy not to release details of UK Rules of Engagement as to do so would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758118/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:28:48.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758118/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758118/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-06","Islamic State: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the UK's rules of engagement are for Operation Inherent Resolve (a) overall and (b) in relation to planned and reactive strikes as part of combat air patrols.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","9248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758120","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-15","<p>The Ministry of Defence takes its role in promoting International Humanitarian Law and Human Rights Law very seriously. Before we undertake any training of foreign troops around the world, we assess the potential impact of the proposed training in relation to these laws and we seek to mitigate any risks. Our training in Iraq includes instruction on the Law of Armed Conflict. If we are made aware of any credible potential breaches of International Law we engage with the Iraqi authorities.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758120/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T12:09:12.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758120/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758120/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-06","Iraq: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department has taken to ensure that the behaviour of the Iraqi armed forces trained by UK armed forces is compliant with international (a) humanitarian and (b) human rights law.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","9071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758121","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-15","<p>The Ministry of Defence engages the support of British Sign Language interpreters as required. Arrangements are made at a local level.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758121/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T12:07:28.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758121/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758121/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-06","Ministry of Defence: Sign Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department takes to provide (a) information on its services in British Sign Language (BSL) and (b) correspondence in BSL to people whose principal language is BSL.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","9002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758122","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Royal Navy decided to postpone the First Sea Lord's Chatham House Conference that had been planned for 7 July to prioritise the Defence Security and Equipment International 2017 exhibition as a better opportunity for discussion about the new era of maritime power.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758122/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:31:55.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758122/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758122/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-06","Shipping: Conferences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the reason was for cancelling the Maritime Conference at Chatham House on 7 July 2017.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","9042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758123","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-14","<p>I will make an announcement on the way forward in due course.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758123/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:31:25.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758123/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758123/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-06","Armed Forces: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to publish (a) his Department's response to the Better Combat Compensation consultation and (b) the submissions made to that consultation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","9046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758124","Department for Education","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Department publishes information on its services on GOV.UK. This content meets legal accessibility requirements and can be read by assistive technology.</p><p> </p><p>Documents published by the department can be requested in an alternative format in line with the Equalities Act 2010, this includes British Sign Language.</p><p> </p><p>The Department can also engage with correspondence from individuals using British Sign Language if that is the preferred format.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is committed to ensuring young people who use British Sign Language gain the skills they need. In January 2017, we announced that for the first time, British Sign Language will be accepted as an alternative qualification to functional skills in English for apprentices where BSL is their first language.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758124/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T09:09:29.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758124/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758124/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Department for Education: Sign Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department takes to provide (a) information on its services in British Sign Language (BSL) and (b) correspondence in BSL to people whose principal language is BSL.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","9003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758125","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>At present, there are no plans to introduce any further GCSEs beyond those to which the Government has already committed.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758125/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T14:27:27.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758125/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758125/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Sign Language: GCSE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will encourage exam boards to offer GCSEs in British Sign Language.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","9014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758126","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>Access to fee and maintenance loans from the Student Loan Company (SLC) is currently restricted for students wishing to study qualifications that are at an equivalent or lower level to those which they already hold. These are known as Equivalent or Lower Qualifications (ELQ). There are exemptions to these restrictions, including from 2017/18 for all part-time STEM degree courses (which had been eligible for fee support only).</p><p> </p><p>Full-time STEM student numbers increased between 2003 and 2015, in some cases dramatically (notably in Biological Sciences by 87%, Maths by 78% and Physical Sciences by 77%). Across most STEM subjects, levels of sustained employment have also grown either in line with the average or above the average, and average earnings have increased by well above the 11% graduate average. Evidence suggests the last round of Government capital funding for STEM higher education has led to increases in provision.</p><p> </p><p>We will be carefully monitoring the impact of lifting the ELQ exemption for part-time STEM courses in the context of our assessments of higher education STEM and demand overall.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758126/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:19:48.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758126/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758126/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","STEM Subjects: Higher Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will extend the number of courses covered by the exemption to the Equivalent Level Qualification rules to include full-time undergraduate STEM courses.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","9025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758127","Department for Education","false","2017-09-15","<p>The Government has reformed the way students studying nursing, midwifery or one of the allied health professions are funded by moving them onto the standard student support system. Training costs have, until now, largely been borne by the NHS. This has resulted in an artificial capping of trainees in these professions. By placing healthcare students on the same support system as other students, Government has removed this cap. On 1 August 2017, the Department for Health announced funding for an extra 10,000 places for nurses, midwives and allied health professionals by 2020, meaning universities can recruit more home-grown talent from the thousands of applications that have needed to be rejected each year. The changes to funding also mean students will have around 25% more financial support than before.</p><p> </p><p>The Government continues to work with the university sector, clinical providers and other partners to support student recruitment.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758127/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T13:53:29.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758127/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758127/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Nurses: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to increase the intake of students on university nursing courses.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","9074"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758128","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>Figures on the proportion of children eligible for free school meals are published annually for all authorities and regions in England. The figures can be found in the statistical first releases, which are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-school-and-pupil-numbers" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-school-and-pupil-numbers</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758128/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:29:08.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758128/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758128/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Free School Meals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of children in (a) Newcastle upon Tyne, (b) the North East and (c) England were entitled to receive free school meals in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","9049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758129","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>The proportion of pupils eligible for, and claiming, free school meals under the pre-universal free school meals system is published at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2017</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758129/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:29:51.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758129/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758129/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Free School Meals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the proportion of infant pupils in (a) Newcastle upon Tyne, (b) the North East and (c) England who would currently be entitled to receive free school meals under the pre-universal free school meals system.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","9050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758130","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Government is taking the impact from the tragic Grenfell Tower fire very seriously. Building owners across the public sector estate have been contacted to ensure any risks are managed and dealt with appropriately and promptly. As set out in our anouncement of 13 July, we have contacted all bodies responsible for fire safety – including in schools and FE colleges - instructing them to carry out checks to identify any buildings which may require further investigation.</p><p>Two schools to date – one a secondary school, one a primary special school - where Aluminium Composite Material (ACM) cladding has been identified and tested, have been alerted to the results. Five FE colleges have been identified as having ACM cladding – in one case, the building affected is shared with a university.</p><p>All these school and college buildings have been inspected by the Fire and Rescue Service - who confirmed appropriate measures are in place to mitigate the risks from potential fire. The buildings have now been declared safe for use. We are continuing to work closely with the schools concerned to support them and ensure all the necessary steps are taken to ensure the continued safety of the buildings.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758130/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:59:32.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758130/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758130/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Educational Institutions: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what information her Department holds on (a) primary schools, (b) secondary schools and (c) further education colleges which are clad in flammable substances.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","9052"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758131","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>The proportion of pupils eligible for, and claiming, free school meals under the pre-universal free school meals system is published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2017</a></p><p>Data is not summarised by parliamentary constituency. Data for each school is, however, available via the link to underlying tables (quoted above). then entering the file named ‘Schools_Pupils_UD’.</p><p>The relevant figures can be filtered by school phase, school type and parliamentary constituency.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758131/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:31:15.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758131/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758131/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Free School Meals: Stockton North","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether her Department has made an estimate of how many families in Stockton North constituency would be entitled to free school meals under the pre-universal free school meals system; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","9099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758132","Department for Education","false","2017-09-15","<p>The Government wants to improve careers education and guidance for all ages. We are investing over £70 million this year to support young people and adults to get high quality careers provision.</p><p> </p><p>The Careers &amp; Enterprise Company (CEC) has made excellent progress to date in several areas, including:</p><ul><li>launching its Enterprise Adviser Network to provide more opportunities for young people to learn about the world of work. To date over 1,800 Enterprise Advisers are working with schools and colleges to support their careers and enterprise strategies and link up with employers.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>an investment fund which is helping proven careers and enterprise activities to reach 250,000 young people, with 75% going to the geographical areas most in need of support.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>providing funding for 39 mentoring programmes that support young people most at risk of not achieving their potential.</li></ul><p> </p><p>We remain committed to working with the CEC in the future and building on the good work carried out to date.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758132/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T11:25:41.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758132/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758132/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Careers and Enterprise Company","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment her Department has made of the work of the Careers and Enterprise Company to help young people into work; and whether her Department plans to provide support to that company in future.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","9250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758133","Department for Education","false","2017-09-12","<p>Data from the Childcare and early years providers survey (2016) shows that, at the time of the survey, there were 46,600 registered childminders of which 98% were female and 2% male. Latest data on males in full day care settings, the childcare and early years providers survey 2013, showed that they also make up 2% of the workforce. At the time of both surveys the 30 hours of free childcare for three and four year olds policy details were still in development and so we do not have workforce data relating to that provision.</p><p> </p><p><strong><em>To note: </em></strong></p><p>The Childcare and Early Years Providers Survey 2016 is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-and-early-years-providers-survey-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-and-early-years-providers-survey-2016</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The Childcare and Early Years Providers Survey 2013 is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-and-early-years-providers-survey-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-and-early-years-providers-survey-2013</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758133/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-12T16:38:12.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758133/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758133/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many (a) women and (b) men (i) work as childminders or (ii) are employed by childcare providers which are set to deliver the 30 hours of free childcare for three and four year olds.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","9197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758134","Department for Education","false","2017-09-13","<p>We know that high quality early years education helps to give children the best start in life. The quality of early years provision has continued to rise in recent years and the latest figures from Ofsted show that 93% of providers were rated “good” or “outstanding”, as at 31 March 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Staff qualifications have been consistently identified as a predictor of higher quality in early years provision, particularly graduate-level qualifications. For this reason the Department published the Early Years Workforce Strategy in March to support the development of a well-qualified workforce with the appropriate knowledge, skills and experience to deliver high quality early education and childcare for children from birth to age five. Commitments in the workforce strategy include: improving the quality of early years training, level 2 qualifications and providing access to continuous professional development. The Early years Workforce Strategy is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/early-years-workforce-strategy" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/early-years-workforce-strategy</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758134/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T15:53:41.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758134/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758134/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans she has to ensure the ongoing high quality of childcare; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","9198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758135","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>Schools have the freedom to plan their curriculum time to best meet the need of their pupils and it is the decision of individual schools whether English language and English literature are taught separately or together.</p><p>The Department believes that the two subjects should be examined separately as the previous combined English GCSE did not allow pupils to demonstrate their knowledge and understanding in either English language or English literature in sufficient depth or breadth.</p><p>English language and English literature are counted separately in the performance tables as separate qualifications. In 2016, Progress 8 was introduced as a headline measure of secondary school performance to compare the progress pupils make across eight subjects. Progress 8 focuses on an academic core, and both English language and English literature can be double weighted to signify their importance. In order to qualify for double weighting in English, a pupil needs to be entered to sit both GCSE English language and GCSE English literature. If a pupil sits both qualifications, the highest grade achieved in either GCSE English language or GCSE English literature will be double weighted for the English element of Progress 8.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758135/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:58:48.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758135/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758135/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","English Language and Literature: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what guidance her Department provides to schools and examination boards on whether English language and English literature should be (a) taught, (b) examined and (c) reflected in school tables separately; and what the practice is of state schools.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","9252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758136","Department for Education","false","2017-09-14","<p>Kensington Aldridge Academy has delayed the start of its academic school year until Monday 11 September, with a week of off-site residential activities. It will open in its new temporary buildings off nearby Scrubs Lane on Monday 18 September. The expectation is that the vast majority of pupils will be able to start the school year.</p><p>The on-going work at Grenfell Tower itself will clearly determine when the school can return to its permanent premises, but we do not currently expect that to be before the summer term of this academic year.</p><p>St Francis of Assisi Primary School returned to its premises on 26 June. School admissions are managed at a local level. In this situation we are in regular contact with the Tri-Borough Admissions Team for Westminster, Hammersmith &amp; Fulham and the Royal Borough of Kensington &amp; Chelsea, and at this time we have not been made aware of parents of any children attending St Francis of Assisi requesting to move to an alternative school.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","9156 ; 9157","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758136/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T07:59:10.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758136/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758136/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 25 July 2017 to Question 5173, how many school children at Kensington Aldridge Academy have been unable to begin the academic school year 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","9155"
