"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758209","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>Figures are available from 2011-12 when the budgetary framework and Departmental group structure was changed as a result of the Constitutional Reform and Governance Act 2010.</p><p>The transfers from the Department’s Capital Departmental Expenditure Limit (CDEL) to the Revenue Departmental Expenditure Limit (RDEL) are set out below. No transfers were made between 2011-12 and 2013-14.</p><p>2014-15:</p><p>- £640 million was transferred from the Department’s CDEL budget to the RDEL.</p><p> </p><p>2015-16:</p><p>- £950 million was transferred from the Department’s CDEL budget to the RDEL.</p><p> </p><p>2016-17:</p><p>- £1,200 million was transferred from the Department’s CDEL budget to the RDEL.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758209/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T13:01:07.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758209/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758209/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","NHS: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much funding from the public purse that was allocated to capital accounts in the NHS has been transferred to revenue accounts in each of the last 10 years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758210","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>National Health Service commissioners and providers need to work together to manage demand and plan sufficient capacity to maintain low waiting times. Referral management and assessment services can be a highly effective way of ensuring only those patients who need to go to hospital do so. Commissioners use referral management centres, as well as clinical triage and assessment centres, to ensure patients are treated by the most appropriate clinical professional as quickly as possible. It does not make sense for patients to be referred to hospital directly when they can be more appropriately (and more quickly) treated elsewhere.</p><p> </p><p>Referral management and assessment services should only be in place where they carry clinical support and provide benefits to patients. They must not be devices that delay treatment or lead to waiting times not being properly recorded.</p><p> </p><p>It is for individual clinical commissioning groups to assess the effectiveness of the services provided by referral management schemes in line with the contracts held to provide these services.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758210/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T10:58:03.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758210/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758210/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Hospitals: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of private sector referral management schemes.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9059"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758211","Department of Health","false","2017-09-15","<p>The Department collects data on backlog maintenance (the capital investment needed to bring the estate and facilities to an appropriate standard for quality and safety) annually from National Health Service trusts through its Estates Returns Information Collection. The data collected is not amended centrally and its accuracy always remains the responsibility of the contributing NHS organisations. It can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/559126/est-ret-info-col-2015-2016-Report.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/559126/est-ret-info-col-2015-2016-Report.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>NHS organisations use a risk-based methodology to categorise backlog maintenance. This allows any high risk elements related to health and safety to be prioritised by trusts for urgent attention, whilst investment to eradicate lower priority backlog can be timed so that any disruption to clinical services caused by the building works is minimised.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758211/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T12:20:22.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758211/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758211/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","NHS: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the recent trends in the NHS high-risk maintenance backlog; and what steps he is taking to tackle that backlog.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758212","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>Sustainability and transformation partnerships (STPs) are not statutory organisations, but a way for the National Health Service and local government to work together. The STP process does not alter the existing accountabilities of clinical commissioning groups (CCGs), local authorities and NHS provider organisations.</p><p>Each STP footprint has agreed its own governance and representation, depending on local circumstances to ensure that all relevant NHS bodies and partners are included. CCGs are a fundamental part of a STP and are bound by this agreed governance arrangement.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758212/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T14:30:18.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758212/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758212/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Clinical Commissioning Groups: Sustainability and Transformation Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether individual clinical commissioning groups are required to comply with the majority decision of a sustainability and transformation plan board.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758213","Department of Health","false","2017-09-15","<p>We understand from NHS England that currently, seven out of the 16 exemplar trusts (44%) use IT systems supplied by Cerner and are listed in the following table.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Cerner exemplar trust List</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cambridge University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust with Chelsea and Westminster NHS Foundation Trust</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Newcastle upon Type Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oxford University Hospitals NHS Trust (and Nuffield Orthopaedic Centre NHS Trust)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Free Hampstead NHS Trust</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>West Suffolk NHS Foundation Trust</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wirral University Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758213/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T13:35:20.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758213/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758213/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","NHS Trusts: Cerner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many and what proportion of IT exemplar trusts use IT systems supplied by Cerner.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758214","Department of Health","false","2017-09-11","<p>The National Health Service Wi-Fi programme will meet the commitment to provide free Wi-Fi for patients across the NHS estate.</p><p> </p><p>As part of this work, the programme has liaised with providers of hospital bedside entertainment services; and we are advised that these services will not impact on hospitals’ provision of free Wi-Fi services.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758214/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:16:14.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758214/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758214/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Hospitals: Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effect of the provision of bedside television and bedside telephones in NHS hospitals on the installation of broadband services for NHS patients.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","9034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758215","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence is the independent, expert body responsible for developing authoritative, evidence-based guidance for the National Health Service on whether drugs and other treatments represent an effective use of NHS resources. The methods and processes it uses in the development of its guidance are internationally respected and have been developed through extensive engagement with a full range of stakeholders, including the Department, and are periodically reviewed to ensure that they remain fit for purpose.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758215/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T14:12:16.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758215/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758215/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Rare Diseases: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the NICE process for reviewing new treatments for rare diseases.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","9043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758216","Department of Health","false","2017-09-11","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758216/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:08:22.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758216/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758216/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","In Vitro Fertilisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many clinical commissioning groups in England follow in full the guidance provided to them by NICE on the provision of IVF treatment.","false","Biography information for Colleen Fletcher","Coventry North East","Colleen Fletcher","9017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758217","Department of Health","false","2017-09-11","<p>We do not currently collect data on the number of allied health professionals occupying leadership positions in the National Health Service. However we understand that around half of NHS trust Chief Executives have a clinical background and that a small number are allied health professionals.</p><p> </p><p>The Faculty of Medical Leadership and Management conducted a review of the opportunities and barriers facing clinicians who wish to move in to senior operational leadership roles in the NHS. The review has been submitted to the Department and a response will be published in due course. We would be happy to meet with the Allied Health Professions Federation to discuss this matter.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","9020","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758217/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:56:04.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758217/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758217/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Health Professions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of Allied Health Professionals in leadership roles in the NHS; and if he will meet representatives of the Allied Health Professions Federation to discuss this matter.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","9019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758218","Department of Health","false","2017-09-11","<p>We do not currently collect data on the number of allied health professionals occupying leadership positions in the National Health Service. However we understand that around half of NHS trust Chief Executives have a clinical background and that a small number are allied health professionals.</p><p> </p><p>The Faculty of Medical Leadership and Management conducted a review of the opportunities and barriers facing clinicians who wish to move in to senior operational leadership roles in the NHS. The review has been submitted to the Department and a response will be published in due course. We would be happy to meet with the Allied Health Professions Federation to discuss this matter.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","9019","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758218/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:56:04.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758218/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758218/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Health Professions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what representations he has received from the Allied Health Professions Federation in response to his consultation on leadership in the NHS; and what his response was to these representations.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","9020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758219","Department of Health","false","2017-09-15","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>We have made significant progress since our focus on sepsis increased in January 2015. The Commissioning for Quality and Innovation Scheme for sepsis incentivises providers to improve identification and timely treatment of sepsis – since the scheme was launched in 2015, we estimate more than 998 lives have been saved.</p><p> </p><p>A new national action plan (for 2017/18) was published on 13 September to update the action plan originally launched in October 2015. It will include embedding safety netting with all healthcare professionals assessing patients with infections, supporting a range of education and training resources developed by Health Education England and further work on improving standards and reporting.</p><p> </p><p>The new ambition to halve healthcare associated Gram-negative bloodstream infections (BSIs) by 2020, arising from our response to Lord O’Neill’s recommendations in relation to Antimicrobial Resistance, also contribute to reductions in sepsis as patients with Gram-negative BSIs may well go on to develop sepsis. This work is led by NHS Improvement and is focusing in 2017/18 on reducing E. coli BSIs – almost half of these arise from urinary tract infections.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758219/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T11:15:54.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758219/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758219/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Urinary Tract Infections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients with urinary tract infections went on to contract sepsis in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758220","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>As of May 2017 there are 2,632 full time equivalent healthcare scientists working in the area of Cellular Sciences, which includes Cellular Pathology. The Department is committed to improving cancer services, including through investment in the diagnostic workforce. Health Education England has committed to publishing a cancer workforce plan before the end of the year.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758220/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T10:45:36.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758220/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758220/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Pathology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure adequate levels of cellular pathology staff in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758221","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) produced a Quality Standard (QS90) in 2015 in order to advise upon the diagnosis, management and treatment of urinary tract infections in adults to a high quality of care. It includes assessment, antibiotic treatment and referral for specialist assessment. It describes high-quality care and priority areas for improvement.</p><p> </p><p>NICE reviewed the Quality Standard in 2016 and determined that it was still effective and up to date.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758221/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T14:12:25.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758221/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758221/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Urinary Tract Infections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the recommended antibiotic treatment for urinary tract infections.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758222","Department of Health","false","2017-09-11","<p>The global WannaCry cyber attack in May 2017 has reaffirmed the potential for cyber incidents to impact directly on patient care and the need for our health and care system to act decisively to minimise the impact on essential front-line services. Weak passwords were not a vulnerability exploited in the WannaCry attack.</p><p> </p><p>Passwords are one element of ensuring the cyber security of National Health Service organisations, and improving them is part of a wider set of standards as introduced in the Government’s response Your Data: Better Security, Better Choice, Better Care published on 12 July 2017. The Government’s response accepts the 10 Data Security Standards recommended by the National Data Guardian. A copy of the response is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/government-responds-on-cyber-security-and-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/government-responds-on-cyber-security-and-data</a></p><p> </p><p>The NHS contract has been changed so that NHS organisations are formally required to adopt data security standards including security training for staff and annual reviews of processes.</p><p>NHS Digital is supporting local organisations to strengthen cyber security by sharing best practice across the health and care system and carrying out on-site assessments.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758222/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T14:37:53.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758222/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758222/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","NHS: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department has taken to improve the security of NHS passwords since the WannaCry cyber attack in May 2017.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","9272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758223","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>The Scientific Advisory Committee on Nutrition has recently updated the evidence on folic acid in response to a request from Food Standards Scotland, and reiterated its support for mandatory folic acid fortification, provided that this is introduced alongside restrictions on voluntary fortification of foods with folic acid. Ministers are currently considering the issue of mandatory fortification of flour and will respond in due course.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","8626","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758223/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T16:17:28.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758223/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758223/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Flour: Folic Acid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the Government's policy is on the fortification of flour with folic acid.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","9208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758224","Department of Health","false","2017-09-11","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758224/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:05:04.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758224/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758224/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","NHS Walk-in Centres: Diabetes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many walk-in clinics are in operation; and how many such clinics offer specialist diabetic care.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","9296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758225","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Scrap Metal Dealers Act 2013 which introduced a regulatory licensing scheme for scrap metal dealers that had seen a significant reduction in metal theft from 62,457 offences in 2012/13 to 16,155 in 2015/16.</p><p>The provisions contained in the legislation have been generally welcomed and supported by industry partners and sole traders and there are tough measures in the legislation to tackle the activities of those who operate outside the law.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758225/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-12T16:29:00.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758225/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758225/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Scrap Metal Dealers Act 2013: Sole Traders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment her Department has made of the effect of the Scrap Metal Dealers Act 2013 on sole traders.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","9185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758226","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>We will be publishing the review of the Scrap Metal Dealers Act 2013 shortly.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758226/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:19:56.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758226/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758226/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Scrap Metal Dealers Act 2013","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how and when she plans to report on the findings of the review of the Scrap Metal Dealers Act 2013.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","9186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758227","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Home Office does not publish data on any in country applications for leave from EU nationals, but does publish information on a small number of out of country visa applications and grants. The latest published data can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017/list-of-tables#visas" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017/list-of-tables#visas</a></p><p> </p><p>EU nationals benefit from a right to reside in the UK which is derived from Directive 2004/38/EC (‘the Free Movement Directive’), as implemented by the Immigration (European Economic Area) Regulations 2016. This legislation does not require EU nationals to hold any form of leave under the UK’s domestic Immigration Rules in order to remain in the UK. However, they can apply for leave to remain if they wish.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758227/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:32:19.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758227/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758227/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many EU citizens applied for leave to remain in the UK in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","9292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758228","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The migration transparency data does not directly answer the question, but does show performance against service standards for routes that have them, and work in progress volumes for all routes.</p><p>It can be found here - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-august2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-august-2017</a></p><p>The data at table at InC_05 does not breakdown into specific case types and will include non human rights cases.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758228/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T14:36:47.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758228/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758228/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average processing time was for immigration applications that fell outside service standards because they raised human rights issues between 1 September 2016 and 31 August 2017.","false","Biography information for Meg Hillier","Hackney South and Shoreditch","Meg Hillier","9268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758229","Home Office","false","2017-10-04","<p>The specific data requested is not published by the Home Office.</p><p> </p><p>Published data on visa processing times, including the percentage of visas processed within published service standards, is published online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data</a> (then listed by publication date under ‘UK Visas &amp; Immigration’).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758229/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-04T13:43:01.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758229/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758229/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of applications for settlement visas paid for under her Department's Priority Service Scheme were processed within 60 working days in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","9242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758230","Home Office","false","2017-10-04","<p>The data is not recorded centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Published statistics on visa applications in the Family category can be found online at the following address: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/638590/entry-visas1-apr-jun-2017-tables.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/638590/entry-visas1-apr-jun-2017-tables.ods</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","9041","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758230/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-04T13:47:49.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758230/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758230/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many of the refugee family reunion visas granted on the basis of exceptional compelling compassionate circumstances outside the immigration rules were under 18, for each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Angus Brendan MacNeil","9040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758231","Home Office","false","2017-10-04","<p>The data is not recorded centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Published statistics on visa applications in the Family category can be found online at the following address: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/638590/entry-visas1-apr-jun-2017-tables.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/638590/entry-visas1-apr-jun-2017-tables.ods</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","9040","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758231/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-04T13:47:50.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758231/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758231/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many refugee family reunion visas were granted to children, by country of origin, for each year for which records are available.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Angus Brendan MacNeil","9041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758232","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>Statistics on specific constituencies are not published and cannot be obtained electronically.</p><p> </p><p>Published data relating to extensions of leave to remain is available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","9022","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758232/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:56:57.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758232/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758232/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Immigration: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been classified as having no recourse to public funds in (a) Camberwell and Peckham constituency and (b) the London Borough of Southwark in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","9018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758233","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>Statistics on specific constituencies are not published and cannot be obtained electronically.</p><p> </p><p>Published data relating to extensions of leave to remain is available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","9018","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758233/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:56:57.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758233/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758233/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Immigration: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people with dependents have been classified as having no recourse to public funds in (a) Camberwell and Peckham constituency and (b) the London Borough of Southwark in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","9022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758234","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The allocation of resources is an operational decision for Chief Constables, working with their Police and Crime Commissioners. The information is not held centrally by the Home Office.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758234/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:22:34.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758234/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758234/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","West Yorkshire Police: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate her Department has made of the cost to West Yorkshire Police of providing support to people with mental health needs.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","9035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758235","Home Office","false","2018-02-21","<p>The Department publishes information on its services on GOV.UK. Documents we publish can be requested in an alternative format, in line with the Equalities Act 2010, and this includes British Sign Language.</p><p>When hosting staff events we provide a British Sign Language signer where one has been requested in advance.</p><p>We have existing frameworks in place to provide communication support services which includes BSL Interpreters. In circumstances where this service is not suitable for the individuals requirements we have arrangements in place to provide alternative support though the Crown Commercial Service framework agreements.</p><p>We ask our customers if they require any reasonable adjustments and aim to meet their bespoke needs.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758235/answer",,,,,,,,,"2018-02-21T11:26:03.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758235/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758235/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Home Office: Sign Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department takes to provide (a) information on its services in British Sign Language (BSL) and (b) correspondence in BSL to people whose principal language is BSL.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","9007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758236","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>I am sorry but we do not hold the data required to answer the question in the requested format.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office regularly shares information with UNHCR, relating to stateless applications and decisions made. The information provided is published by UNHCR, in regular trend reports. The latest published report by UNHCR on mid year trends June 2016 can be found at link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.unhcr.org/uk/statistics/unhcrstats/58aa8f247/mid-year-trends-june-2016.html" target="_blank">http://www.unhcr.org/uk/statistics/unhcrstats/58aa8f247/mid-year-trends-june-2016.html</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","9032 ; 9086 ; 9087","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758236/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:50:34.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758236/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758236/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, of applicants who were refused leave to remain as a stateless person since April 2013, how many were recognised as stateless persons but not considered eligible for leave to remain.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","9031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758237","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>I am sorry but we do not hold the data required to answer the question in the requested format.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office regularly shares information with UNHCR, relating to stateless applications and decisions made. The information provided is published by UNHCR, in regular trend reports. The latest published report by UNHCR on mid year trends June 2016 can be found at link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.unhcr.org/uk/statistics/unhcrstats/58aa8f247/mid-year-trends-june-2016.html" target="_blank">http://www.unhcr.org/uk/statistics/unhcrstats/58aa8f247/mid-year-trends-june-2016.html</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","9031 ; 9086 ; 9087","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758237/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:50:34.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758237/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758237/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications for leave to remain as a stateless person have been received each year from April 2013 to present; and how many such applications were (a) granted, (b) refused, (c) declared invalid, (d) withdrawn, (e) still pending after six months, (f) still pending after 12 months and (g) still pending after 18 months.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","9032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758238","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Home Office does not report on or publish this data.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758238/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:55:27.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758238/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758238/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications for British citizenship for people recognised as stateless the naturalisation or registration fee has been waived or reduced in the last five years; and of these how many were (a) for applicants under 18 years, (b) for applicants under 22 years at the time of application and applying under Paragraph 3, Schedule 2 of the British Nationality Act 1981 and (c) adult naturalisation applications under section 6 of the British Nationality Act 1981.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","9033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758239","Home Office","false","2017-09-15","<p>I refer my Hon. Friend to the answer given to the Hon. Member for East Renfrewshire on 28 June 2017, UIN 556.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758239/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T13:15:36.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758239/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758239/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Hezbollah","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will extend the proscription of the military wing of Hezbollah under the provisions of the Terrorism Act 2000 to include its political wing.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","8994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758240","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>There are a range of existing powers available for both the police and local authorities to tackle unauthorised encampments. The Criminal Justice and Public Order Act 1994 provides specific powers to the police to move travellers from unauthorised encampments if certain criteria are met.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office works closely with the police to ensure the powers they have are fit for purpose. However, the decision on when and whether to use police powers is an independent operational decision for the police.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758240/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:16:52.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758240/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758240/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to ensure that police forces and chief constables enforce Section 61 of the Criminal Justice and Public Order Act 1994 in relation to the combatting of illegal Travellers' sites.","false","Biography information for Jack Lopresti","Filton and Bradley Stoke","Jack Lopresti","8997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758241","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The specific data requested is not published by the Home Office.</p><p> </p><p>Published data on visa processing times, including the percentage of visas processed within published service standards, is published at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data</a> (then listed by publication date under ‘UK Visas &amp; Immigration’).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758241/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-12T09:52:36.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758241/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758241/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Visas: India","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average length of time taken to process an application for a priority settlement visa in New Delhi was in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","9224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758242","Home Office","false","2017-10-04","<p>The specific data requested is not published by the Home Office.</p><p> </p><p>Published data on visa processing times, including the percentage of visas processed within published service standards, is published online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data</a> (then listed by publication date under ‘UK Visas &amp; Immigration’).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758242/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-04T13:50:55.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758242/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758242/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of applications for non-settlement visas paid for under her Department's Priority Service scheme were processed within 15 working days in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","9123"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758243","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>No decisions have been taken on the police funding formula and no new funding formula will be put in place ahead of a public consultation.</p><p>However, we have recently written to police leaders setting out a programme of engagement to better understand the impact of changing demands on the sector.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758243/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-12T11:57:47.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758243/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758243/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Police: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether it remains her policy to reform the police funding formula.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","9229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758244","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>UK Visas and Immigration consider all requests for refunds on a case by case basis. Whether a refund is issued will depend on the specific circumstances of each case.</p><p>Requests should be made via the complaints process:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-visas-and-immigration/about/complaints-procedure#how-to-complain" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-visas-and-immigration/about/complaints-procedure#how-to-complain</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758244/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-18T13:04:12.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758244/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758244/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 20 July 2017 to Question 5241, what her Department's definition is of an exceptional circumstance that would validate a refund to people who have submitted a visa application under her Department's Priority Service scheme.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","9158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758245","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Government has been clear on its policy on public sector pay since the 2011 Autumn Statement. Home Office representatives attend Police Staff Council and have reflected that position over time.</p><p> </p><p>Police staff pay awards are not subject to approval by the Home Secretary or any other representative of the Home Office.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758245/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:15:53.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758245/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758245/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Police: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will publish the advice given by her Department's representative on the Police Staff Council on the one per cent public sector pay cap at meetings of that Council since the 2011 Autumn Statement.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","9159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758246","Home Office","false","2017-10-04","<p>The specific data requested is not published by the Home Office.</p><p> </p><p>The latest published migration statistics, which includes data on visa application volumes, can be found online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758246/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-10-04T13:49:39.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758246/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758246/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of (a) settlement, (b) non-settlement and (c) total visa applications are submitted under her Department's Priority Service scheme.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","9196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758247","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>Since 2014, Immigration Enforcement has prosecuted one individual in Northern Ireland for employing an individual(s) subject to immigration control. Prior to 2014, the Home Office did not hold this information centrally and it could only now be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758247/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:33:01.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758247/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758247/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Undocumented Workers: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many firms have been prosecuted on more than one separate occasion in Northern Ireland for employing staff who did not have a legal right to be in the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","9251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758248","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Home Office collects information from police forces on the number of police recorded offences that have an online element. The online flag became mandatory from April 2015 therefore data prior to this are not available.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the number of child sexual offences flagged as having an online element are published as experimental statistics in the ONS ‘Crime in England and Wales’ quarterly bulletins. The ‘child sexual offences’ category includes sexual grooming. Information on sexual grooming is not separately published.</p><p> </p><p>These data can be found in table E12 of the experimental tables on the ONS website: <a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/crimeandjustice/datasets/crimeinenglandandwalesexperimentaltables" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/crimeandjustice/datasets/crimeinenglandandwalesexperimentaltables</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office does not hold information on the number of online child grooming offences which have led to prosecutions. The Ministry of Justice are responsible for prosecutions data.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758248/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:25:04.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758248/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758248/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Offences against Children: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many reports of online child grooming have been received by the police in each of the last five years; and how many convictions for online child grooming have been made in each such year.","false","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","9249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758249","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>It is not possible to provide figures as to do so would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758249/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:47:47.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758249/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758249/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many EU nationals of each nationality have been prevented from entering the UK since 2010; and what the reasons were for their entry being refused.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","9127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758250","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>Border Force does not record ethnicity details for those prevented from entering the UK. Therefore it is not possible to establish this information.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758250/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:46:18.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758250/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758250/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many EU nationals of each ethnic group have been prevented from entering the UK since 2010; and what the reasons were for their entry being refused.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","9128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758251","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Home Office does not hold information on the nationality of individuals stopped and searched.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office collects and publishes statistics on the number of stop and searches, and the number of resultant arrests, conducted by each police force in England and Wales. Data are broken down by the reason for the search, and the ethnicity of the person being searched, but not on the nationality of the individual. These data are published in the ‘Police Powers and Procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins, where data for the year ending March 2016 can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2016</a></p><p> </p><p>The next release of ‘Police Powers’ statistics is due to be published in October, for the year ending March 2017.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758251/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:21:32.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758251/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758251/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Stop and Search","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of stop and searches involved (a) foreign and (b) British nationals; and what proportion of each such category resulted in an arrest in the last year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9138"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758252","Home Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Home Office does not hold centrally information on the nationality of individuals arrested. The Home Office collects and publishes data on the number of arrests broken down by offence group, gender, age group and ethnicity. These data are published in the ‘Police Powers and Procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins, where data for the year ending March 2016 can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2016</a></p><p> </p><p>The Home Office does not hold centrally information on the number of arrests that led to a prosecution. Data on prosecutions are the responsibility of the Ministry of Justice.</p><p> </p><p>The next release of ‘Police Powers’ statistics is due to be published in October, for the year ending March 2017.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758252/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T13:23:41.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758252/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758252/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Arrests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of arrests of (a) foreign and (b) British nationals resulted in a prosecution in the last year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758253","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>Citizens of Australia who regularly travel to the UK or hold a UK visa already have the option of becoming a member of the Registered Traveller Service, the benefits of which include use of the ePassport gates.</p><p> </p><p>A complete overview of the service and the eligibility requirements can be found at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/registered-traveller" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/registered-traveller</a>.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758253/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:59:00.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758253/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758253/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Immigration Controls: Australia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to allow visitors from Australia to use e-passport gates as a matter of routine; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg","North East Somerset","Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg","9100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758254","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Government has commissioned the Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to assess the impact of leaving the EU on both seasonal and non-seasonal employment. The MAC will report in September 2018 but may produce interim reports before then.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758254/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:59:50.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758254/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758254/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Seasonal Workers: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the number of non-UK seasonal workers from the EU that are required for the (a) agricultural, (b) construction and (c) hospitality industries after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Anna Soubry","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","9095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758255","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>I am sorry but we do not hold the data required to answer the question in the requested format.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office regularly shares information with UNHCR, relating to stateless applications and decisions made. The information provided is published by UNHCR, in regular trend reports. The latest published report by UNHCR on mid year trends June 2016 can be found at link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.unhcr.org/uk/statistics/unhcrstats/58aa8f247/mid-year-trends-june-2016.html" target="_blank">http://www.unhcr.org/uk/statistics/unhcrstats/58aa8f247/mid-year-trends-june-2016.html</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","9031 ; 9032 ; 9086","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758255/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:50:35.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758255/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758255/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make it her policy to include within published immigration statistics data relating to applications for leave to remain as a stateless person under Part 14 of the Immigration Rules.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","9087"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758256","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>I am sorry but we do not hold the data required to answer the question in the requested format.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office regularly shares information with UNHCR, relating to stateless applications and decisions made. The information provided is published by UNHCR, in regular trend reports. The latest published report by UNHCR on mid year trends June 2016 can be found at link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.unhcr.org/uk/statistics/unhcrstats/58aa8f247/mid-year-trends-june-2016.html" target="_blank">http://www.unhcr.org/uk/statistics/unhcrstats/58aa8f247/mid-year-trends-june-2016.html</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","9031 ; 9032 ; 9087","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758256/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:50:35.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758256/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758256/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-06","Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make it her policy to record and publish data in relation to the number and outcome of applications received from stateless persons each year under paragraph 3, schedule 2 to the British Nationality Act 1981.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","9086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758257","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-13","<p>With 1.8 billion people globally between the ages of 10 and 24, DFID is ensuring that young people are at the centre of all our work, supporting their access to quality education, improved healthcare, and decent work; regardless of their background.</p><p> </p><p>We aim to provide young people with a genuine say in shaping a positive future for their countries. This was illustrated most recently at the 2017 Family Planning summit, which had a Youth Panel that played a key role in setting the agenda and outcomes of the event.</p><p> </p><p>We are also working directly with 5-18 year olds in the UK through our Development Education programme. Through this programme, we are investing in a new generation of Global Britain ambassadors, proud of the work the UK is doing to tackle global poverty, and better prepared to live and eventually work in a globalised economy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758257/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T11:01:37.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758257/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758257/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","International Assistance: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what (a) plans her Department has and (b) funding it has allocated to implement its Youth Agenda, published in April 2016; and how her Department plans to ensure that it works alongside and consults young people as advocates and agents for change.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","9085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758258","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-13","<p>DFID’s new Strategic Vision on Gender Equality will be published and implemented by DFID and with its partners in due course.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758258/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T11:00:54.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758258/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758258/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Gender: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether her Department plans to (a) publish and (b) implement its new Strategic Vision for Gender Equality.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","9084"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758259","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-13","<p>The UK Government’s position on the referendum is clear. Unilateral moves towards independence would not be in the interests of the people of Kurdistan Region, of the rest of Iraq or of wider regional stability. Any referendum or political process towards independence must be agreed with the Government of Iraq in Baghdad. We support a stable, democratic and unified Iraq, one that is able to provide the security, jobs, healthcare and education all Iraqis want and deserve. Ministers and officials are in continuing discussions with both the Government of Iraq and the Kurdistan Regional Government, urging both parties to engage in dialogue to deliver a better future for their people on the basis of the Iraqi Constitution. The Department for International Development has provided £209.5 million in life-saving humanitarian aid to Iraq since June 2014, which has helped to support internally displaced people across Iraq, including those hosted in the Kurdistan region. DFID is working alongside other Government departments to assess the impact of the referendum on our priorities in Iraq.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758259/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T15:54:56.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758259/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758259/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Iraq: Kurds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what contingency planning her Department has undertaken to support Iraqi Kurds in the event of a vote for independence in the forthcoming referendum.","false","Biography information for Jack Lopresti","Filton and Bradley Stoke","Jack Lopresti","9103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758260","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>This is available in the Office for Budgetary Responsibility’s March 2017 Economic and Fiscal Outlook, and can be found in Table 1.2 of the Economy supplementary tables. <a href="http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/download/march-2017-economic-and-fiscal-outlook-supplementary-economy-tables/" target="_blank">http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/download/march-2017-economic-and-fiscal-outlook-supplementary-economy-tables/</a></p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758260/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:31:14.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758260/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758260/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate she has made of the cost to the public purse in cash terms of meeting the target to spend 0.7 per cent of gross national income as development assistance in 2018.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","9253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758261","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>The UK is supporting people in Lebanon by meeting the most urgent humanitarian needs of Syrian refugees and vulnerable host communities, investing in job opportunities and providing quality education to children in Lebanon. Since the start of the Syria crisis, DFID has provided nearly half a million cash grants and vouchers to vulnerable people to meet their basic needs, expanded the Lebanese education system to reach almost 300,000 Syrian children, and improved infrastructure and services in 51 of the most conflict-prone municipalities. We also supported approximately 13,000 individuals in Lebanon through livelihoods projects and support to cooperatives, created 1,300 new jobs and provided sustainable access to clean water and/or sanitation to over 900,000 people.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758261/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:57:32.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758261/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758261/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Syria: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing to Syrian refugees in Lebanon.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","9028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758262","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>The UN co-ordinates the activities of humanitarian actors in Lebanon, including faith-based organisations, in support of the Lebanon Crisis Response Plan, which is a strategic and operational framework agreed by the Government of Lebanon. We encourage all organisations, including church-based initiatives, to ensure any support they provide is coordinated through these appropriate frameworks to ensure the most vulnerable receive the support they need.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758262/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:58:24.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758262/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758262/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Syria: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the effect of church-based initiatives in Lebanon in supporting Syrian refugees.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","9029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758263","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>As of 30 June 2017, 1,001,051 Syrian refugees were registered with UN High Commissioner for Refugees in Lebanon; the Lebanon Crisis Response Plan, agreed between the Government of Lebanon and the UN states that, as not all refugees are registered, the total could be as high as 1.5 million.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758263/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:56:55.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758263/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758263/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Syria: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate she has made of the number of Syrian refugees in Lebanon.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","9027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758264","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-13","<p>DFID provides information and correspondence in British Sign Language (BSL) on request, or when a specific need has been identified.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758264/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T09:56:03.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758264/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758264/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Department for International Development: Sign Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department takes to provide (a) information on its services in British Sign Language (BSL) and (b) correspondence in BSL to people whose principal language is BSL.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","9008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758265","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-13","<p>The arrangements for withdrawal from the EU, including its funds, will be determined as part of the exit negotiations with the European Commission.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758265/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T10:59:30.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758265/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758265/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","International Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans exist for the repatriation or reallocation of the proportion of the overseas aid budget currently contributing towards EU development funds; and whether the Government intends to bring these plans before Parliament.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","9021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758266","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-12","<p>The UK has long been one of the biggest contributors of humanitarian aid for the displaced population in Rakhine State. We have provided over £30 million in humanitarian assistance since 2012, including food and sanitation for over 126,000 people. In the current context access to the worst affected populations is seriously constrained. We are working at the highest levels with the government, other donors and the UN to improve access and ensure that aid reaches those that need it most. DFID has also committed £10.9 million to meet the needs of displaced Rohingya and the host communities who support them in Bangladesh. The UK Government is deeply concerned about the violence against the Rohingya and other communities in Burma’s Rakhine State, and the plight of thousands fleeing their homes.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758266/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-12T09:46:56.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758266/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758266/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Burma: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that sufficient food and medical assistance is being provided to the displaced civilians of Rakine State.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","9048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758267","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-13","<p>DFID has not signed any new contracts or extended any existing contracts with Adam Smith International (ASI) since March 2017. Between 1<sup>st</sup> March – 31<sup>st</sup> August 2017 DFID paid £50.06 million to ASI, to fulfil legally binding contracts. All payments are classified as Official Development Assistance.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758267/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T11:00:04.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758267/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758267/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Adam Smith International","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much funding from the public purse has been paid by her Department to Adam Smith International since March 2017; how much of that funding is classified as Official Development Assistance; and whether her Department has (a) signed any new contracts or (b) extended any existing contracts with Adam Smith International since March 2017.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","9082"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758268","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>In 2015/16 DFID provided £90m in direct assistance to Yemen; in 2016/17 £112m; and in 2017/18 we are providing £139m. On top of this DFID also provides support to Yemen through our global programmes and through our multilateral contributions.</p><p>Our contribution this year makes us the second-largest donor to the UN’s 2017 Yemen Appeal and the third-largest humanitarian donor to Yemen overall. At the same time, the UK continues to play a leading role in lobbying for a political solution to the conflict, as well as pressing the international community to step up their own contributions to Yemen.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758268/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:57:56.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758268/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758268/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Yemen: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much overseas development aid the Government has provided to Yemen since 2015.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","9282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758269","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-13","<p>Between 2011 and 2016, UK aid provided 12 million people with improved access to clean energy, including through off-grid renewable energy and other clean technologies like more efficient cook stoves. This is enabling businesses to be more productive, children to study after school and keeping women and girls safer after dark.</p><p>While DFID funding to energy technologies is informed by the needs of individual countries, the Department retains a strong preference in its bilateral programmes for clean energy solutions. This is consistent with UK leadership internationally, including through the £5.8bn commitment (2016 - 2021) for tackling climate change.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758269/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T09:57:41.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758269/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758269/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-06","Developing Countries: Renewable Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will ensure that two-thirds of UK support for energy access in developing countries is allocated to centralised, renewable electricity and clean cooking solutions.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","9279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758270","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>In line with the Employment Tribunals data retention policy cases from the live databases are archived 12 months after they are concluded and as such personalised data (constituency) is no longer available. In view of this we can only give numbers for claims accepted from October 2016 to March 2017 in line with the published stats.</p><p> </p><p>The table below shows the number of accepted claims against businesses in each of these areas from October 2016 to March 2017.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>Singles</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Multiples</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Jarrow Consituency<sup>1</sup></strong></p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>South Tyneside<sup>2</sup></strong></p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>26</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><sup>1 </sup>Jarrow Constituency taken as accepted claims submitted within the postcode area NE31 &amp; NE32.</p><p><sup>2</sup> South Tyneside taken as accepted claims submitted within the postcode area NE31, NE34, NE10, NE33, NE32, NE36, NE37 &amp; SR6</p><p>Employment Tribunal claims are distributed according to the respondent’s address.</p><p><em>Although care is taken when processing and analysing the data, the details are subject to inaccuracies inherent in any large-scale case management system and is the best data that is available.</em></p><p>The data may differ slightly to that of the published stats as this data was run on a different date.</p><p> </p><p>The data for the North East and UK receipts can be obtained from the published statics using the link: https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/tribunals-and-gender-recognitions-certificates-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2017-and-2016-to-2017.</p><p> </p><p>Due to changes in the type of data published, the regional information was not published previously, as a result data covering 2010 and 2011 have not been provided.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758270/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-12T11:29:07.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758270/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758270/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Employment Tribunals Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many cases have been brought before employment tribunals in (a) Jarrow constituency, (b) South Tyneside, (c) the North East and (d) the UK in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen Hepburn","Jarrow","Mr Stephen Hepburn","9290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758271","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>There are two groups of children who may be held securely, in two jurisdictions. <br>In the family court, a care and supervision order may be made, data in table 4 at https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/family-court-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2017</p><p>In the youth justice estate, the relevant figures are “Total immediate custody” from Table 5.3 of the annual statistics 2015 to 2016: supplementary tables and the “Total custodial remands” from Table 6.1 of the same supplementary tables at: https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/youth-justice-statistics-2015-to-2016</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758271/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:25:06.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758271/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758271/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Children: Secure Accommodation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many court orders for children to be held securely have been made in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","9267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758272","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>Fees in Employment Tribunals raised around £32m after their introduction in 2013. We are now putting in place arrangements to refund those who have paid the fees, which we will be announcing shortly.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758272/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:48:30.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758272/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758272/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Employment Tribunals Service: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of reimbursing people who have paid employment tribunal fees.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","9269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758273","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>Ownership of Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) transferred to new providers in 2015. Contracts with CRCs require each CRC to ensure that it employs a sufficient level of staff, and that its workforce is competent and adequately trained. We no longer routinely collect and publish CRC workforce numbers.</p><p>We closely monitor and robustly manage providers to make sure they fulfil their contractual commitments to reduce reoffending, protect the public and provide value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758273/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:26:59.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758273/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758273/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Community Rehabilitation Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) staff and (b) vacancies there were in each community rehabilitation company in each quarter since those companies were established.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","9270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758274","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-14","<p>The SPACE I report (last published in April 2017) covers incarceration rates for each member country of the Council of Europe: <a href="http://wp.unil.ch/space/files/2017/04/SPACE_I_2015_FinalReport_161215_REV170425.pdf" target="_blank">http://wp.unil.ch/space/files/2017/04/SPACE_I_2015_FinalReport_161215_REV170425.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>Her Majesty’s Prison and Probation Service (HMPPS), routinely publishes average costs per prisoner and prison place, and overall prison unit costs of individual prisons for each private and public sector prison in England and Wales. The information can be accessed in the Prison and Probation Performance Statistics pages for each relevant financial year here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/563326/costs-per-place-cost-per-prisoner-2015-16.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/563326/costs-per-place-cost-per-prisoner-2015-16.pdf</a>. Prison unit costs can be found within the Excel document <em>Costs per prison place and cost per prisoner by individual prison establishment</em> in the ‘Cost by Establishment’ tab. The most recently published figures are for financial year 2015-16 and we expect to publish the 2016-17 data on 26 October 2017.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758274/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:38:38.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758274/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758274/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Prisoners: Per Capita Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the prison incarceration rates per capita are for (a) England and Wales and (b) other EU countries; and what the average cost of jailing a person per year is in (i) England and Wales and (ii) other EU countries.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Angus Brendan MacNeil","9073"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758275","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758275/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:23:26.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758275/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758275/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Family Courts: Perjury","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many cases brought before the family courts have been found to be based on false allegations in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Sir Hugo Swire","9051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758276","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-15","<p>The Ministry has several statutory obligations to provide interpretation and translation in criminal proceedings. This includes a contract for the provision of British Sign Language, which is made available wherever required across the Ministry, its executive agencies and arm length bodies, and other organisations in the justice sector who use the contracts.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758276/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-15T13:11:13.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758276/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758276/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Ministry of Justice: Sign Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department takes to provide (a) information on its services in British Sign Language (BSL) and (b) correspondence in BSL to people whose principal language is BSL.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","9010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758277","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>A redacted version of the new contract between the Ministry of Justice and G4S for electronic monitoring hardware equipment will be published on Contracts Finder in line with current transparency regulations. We are currently planning to sign the contract by the end of October 2017. I will write to the Honourable gentleman when the contract has been published.</p><p>The field monitoring services including fitting and removal of tags and the monitoring provision is provided by Capita Business Services Limited.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758277/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:09:41.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758277/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758277/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","G4S: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will place the documents relating to the contract signed in 2017 between the Government and G4S for the electronic tagging of offenders in the Library.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","9216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758278","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>Maintaining access to justice remains absolutely vital and continues to be at the heart of our reforms. Our legal aid reforms are reducing costs to taxpayers whilst still providing legal help to those who need it most.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the number of defendants with no advocate or unknown representation can be found in table AC11 of the annual Criminal Courts Statistics Quarterly publication (main tables) at the link below:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-court-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-court-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2017</a></p><p> </p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758278/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:44:56.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758278/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758278/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Crown Courts: Legal Representation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have chosen to represent themselves in Crown Court since the implementation of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","9217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758279","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-14","<p>Reliable information on the proportion of foreign and British national defendants of each sex and ethnic group who were refused bail or sentenced to immediate custody could only be provided at disproportionate cost because court proceedings data does not include information on nationality.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","9136","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758279/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:20:11.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758279/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758279/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Prison Sentences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of (a) foreign and (b) British national defendants of each (i) sex and (ii) ethnic group were sentenced to immediate custody for each offence type in the last year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758280","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-14","<p>I am currently considering the planned post-implementation review of recent legal aid reforms. I will make an announcement in due course.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758280/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:22:11.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758280/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758280/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Legal Aid Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, on what date the Government plans to publish its review into legal aid reform.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","9112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758281","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-14","<p>I am currently considering the planned post-implementation review of recent legal aid reforms. I will make an announcement in due course.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758281/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:23:03.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758281/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758281/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Legal Aid Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will list (a) the organisations and (b) people who have given evidence to the Government's review into legal aid reform; and if he will publish that evidence.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","9113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758282","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Court Act of 2003 Part 4 (54) provides the court security officer acting in the execution of his duty with the power to ask a person to surrender an article that may be evidence or in relation to an offence. It is an offence to take a photograph or recording in court and therefore the person will be asked to surrender the device by the court security officer. If this takes place within a court/hearing room this will be upon the direction of the judge.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758282/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:26:18.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758282/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758282/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Courts: Recordings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what power a court has to require a person to hand over a device if that device has been seen to have been used or is thought to have been used to take a photograph or recording in court.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758283","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Court Act of 2003, Part 4 (52) provides the court security officer acting in the execution of his duty with the powers to search any person who is in a court building, and any article in their possession. If a person is thought to have used a device to take a photograph or recording in court, and they refuse to surrender that device, the court security officer may search that person. If this takes place within a court/hearing room this will be upon the direction of the judge.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758283/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:30:38.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758283/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758283/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Courts: Recordings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what power a court has to search a person for a device if that device has been seen to have been used or is thought to have been used to take a photograph or recording in court.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758284","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>We do not hold the information requested centrally and it could be obtained only at disproportionate cost.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758284/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T13:36:17.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758284/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758284/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of offenders who re-offended or breached their licence and who were liable to be recalled were not recalled in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758285","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-14","<p>Reliable information on the proportion of foreign and British national defendants of each sex and ethnic group who were refused bail or sentenced to immediate custody could only be provided at disproportionate cost because court proceedings data does not include information on nationality.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","9137","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758285/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:20:11.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758285/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758285/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Bail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of (a) foreign and (b) British national defendants of each (i) sex and (ii) ethnic group were refused bail for each offence type in the last year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758286","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>Families can play a significant role in supporting an offender; positive family relationships have been identified as a protective factor in the desistance from crime. The Government welcomes the recommendations identified by Lord Farmer to strengthen family ties to help offenders turn their lives around and protect public safety.</p><p><br>Work has already commenced on developing a strategy which will take forward recommendations from the review. We are already taking forward some key recommendations, including giving governors the budget and flexibility to spend their resources appropriately to help prisoners keep important family ties.</p><p><br>Alongside this, we plan to pilot new family and significant relationship performance measures which will provide crucial guidance to deliver more consistent services in areas such as visitations across the entire prisons estate.</p><p><br>We will continue to hold regular meetings with Lord Farmer to update him on implementation of his recommendations.</p><p><br>The Government will ensure that Parliament is fully appraised of progress on implementation and will set out its proposals for doing so in a letter to the Chair of the Justice Select Committee in due course.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758286/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:30:10.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758286/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758286/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-06","Prisoners: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he is taking to implement the recommendations of the report by Lord Farmer, The importance of strengthening prisoners' family ties to prevent reoffending and reduce intergenerational crime, published in August 2017.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","9144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758287","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) already promotes trade and investment in support of all regions and nations of the UK. In 2016/17, Northern Ireland secured 34 foreign direct investment projects, creating 1,622 jobs and safeguarding 950 more, and DIT will continue to work closely with the Devolved Administrations to support businesses across the UK.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758287/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T16:29:12.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758287/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758287/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-06","Foreign Investment in UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans he has to ensure that each nation and region can take advantage of the opportunities for trade and inward investment after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","9254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758288","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Electoral Commission does not hold data on the number of voters wrongly excluded from the electoral register at the 2017 UK general election.</p><p> </p><p>The electoral register is managed by individual Electoral Registration Officers (EROs) at local authorities. They are legally responsible for determining if an application to register to vote is from an eligible individual.</p>","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758288/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-11T15:23:44.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758288/answer","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758288/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2017-09-06","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, how many voters were wrongly excluded from the electoral list at the 2017 General Election; and in which constituencies those exclusions took place.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","9114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758289","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>The then Highways Agency assessed the potential merits of introducing heating apparatus in road surfaces in a trial from 2004 to 2007, using heat stored during the summer to heat the road surface in winter.</p><p> </p><p>This helped prevent ice forming by warming the road to keep it above zero degrees centigrade, but was found not to be effective below minus four degrees centigrade. Conventional salt treatments proved to be safer and more cost effective.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758289/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T10:49:05.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758289/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758289/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-06","Roads: Heating","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of introducing heating apparatus in certain road surfaces similar to that installed on the M4 at Chiswick in the 1960s to improve safety in winter and reduce the need for gritting; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","9101"
