"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758368","Department of Health","false","2017-09-19","<p>The future of local acute hospital provision is a matter for NHS England and the National Health Service locally.</p><p> </p><p>Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust advises that it is not currently carrying out a public consultation. However, the Trust is currently engaging with the public on its proposals to move to a single acute specialist facility and to keep most care local. The purpose of this engagement is not focused on specific sites but on the principle of moving to a single acute specialist facility.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758368/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-19T13:54:14.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758368/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758368/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the extent to which the consultation exercise being undertaken by the Epsom and St Helier Trust about the future of local acute hospital provision is consistent with the Cabinet Office’s consultation principles.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758369","Department of Health","false","2017-09-19","<p>Any decision regarding service changes is a matter for NHS England and the National Health Service locally.</p><p> </p><p>The Surrey Heartlands Sustainability and Transformation Plan refers to the need to make progress on an estates solution for Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals but does not make proposals to downgrade or close services at Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758369/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-19T13:55:35.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758369/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758369/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, in the light of the proposal from the Epsom and St Helier Trust to downgrade or close services at Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals to make way for a new acute hospital in Sutton, whether any such proposal has been included in the Surrey Heartlands Sustainability and Transformation Plan.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758370","Department of Health","false","2017-09-19","<p>Any decision regarding service changes is a matter for NHS England and the National Health Service locally.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England advises that the South West London Sustainability and Transformation Plan does not propose the closure of any hospital within its footprint.</p><p> </p><p>In respect of the Leicester, Leicestershire and Rutland Sustainability and Transformation Plan, the document considers a range of options for local services, and where specific proposals are agreed by the local NHS, they will be subject to formal public consultation.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758370/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-19T13:38:22.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758370/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758370/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Hospitals: Closures","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is the status of proposals to close acute hospitals at (1) one in five sites in South West London, and (2) one in three sites in Leicestershire.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758371","Department of Health","false","2017-09-19","<p>Any decisions about new hospitals are for NHS England and the National Health Service locally.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that proposals for a new hospital in South West London are at a very early stage. A Strategic Outline Business Case is being prepared for initial consideration by NHS Improvement.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758371/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-19T13:36:57.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758371/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758371/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-06","Hospitals: Greater London","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what discussions they have held with NHS England over the funding of a proposed new hospital in South West London.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758372","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Government is considering a report from the Public Administration and Constitutional Affairs Committee into the operation of the Business Appointment Rules, and will respond in due course.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758372/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:47:34.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758372/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758372/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-06","Business Interests","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the effectiveness of business appointment rules for former ministers and senior civil servants in ensuring public confidence in the work of government.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758373","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The UK Government is among the most transparent in the world and each Department is responsible for publishing a range of data on its activities. Ministers in the Cabinet Office will be working with departments over the coming months to improve the publication process to ensure we continue to meet our obligations in this important area.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758373/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-14T15:46:21.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758373/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758373/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-06","Government Departments: Disclosure of Information","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking to ensure that government departments meet their obligations to publish transparency data in a timely fashion.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758374","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-18","<p>Ascension Island remains strategically important in supporting the Ministry of Defence (MOD) mission in the South Atlantic. The MOD fully intends to return to Ascension Island following the full restructuring of the runway.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758374/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-18T14:20:18.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758374/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758374/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-06","Ascension Island: Aviation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether, following the completion of scheduled works to the US Airbase Wideawake Airfield on Ascension Island, the RAF will resume their use of that airfield.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL1378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758375","Department for Education","false","2017-09-19","<p>As we have previously stated, the Teaching Excellence Framework <strong>(</strong>TEF) is a voluntary process and the Government, therefore, does not keep a record of providers who have chosen not to participate.</p><p> </p><p>The Higher Education Funding Council for England, who are responsible for delivering the TEF, have published a list of providers who received ratings on their website: <a href="http://www.hefce.ac.uk/tefoutcomes/" target="_blank">http://www.hefce.ac.uk/tefoutcomes/</a>.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758375/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-19T13:07:15.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758375/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758375/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-06","Higher Education: Standards","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answers by Lord Nash on 27 July (HL733) and 9 August (HL734), whether they will now answer the question and list those establishments which were eligible to apply to participate in the Teaching Excellence Framework, but which declined to join this voluntary process.","false","Biography information for Lord Jopling",,"Lord Jopling","HL1379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758376","The Senior Deputy Speaker","false","2017-09-20","<p>The Senior Deputy Speaker has asked me, as Chairman of the Services Committee, to respond on his behalf.</p><p>The price of the English still wine offered in the Peers’ Dining Room and available on request in the Barry Room is £54.00 a bottle. The price of the equivalent standard House of Lords own label wine is £18.00 a bottle. The variance in price arises because the English wine (a pinot noir) has a higher wholesale price, while the House pinot noir is purchased in larger volumes using a long-term contract. The house wine is also sold by the glass at £6.35 for 250ml and £4.80 for 175ml.</p><p>The price of the English sparkling wine offered in the Peers’ Dining Room and available on request in the Barry Room is £55.00 a bottle. The price of the equivalent House of Lords own label champagne is £47.50 a bottle. Neither is sold by the glass in the dining rooms.</p>",,"Lord Laming",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758376/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-20T15:18:34.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758376/answer","Biography information for Lord Laming","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758376/answer",,,,,"204",,"Senior Deputy Speaker (HoL)","2017-09-06","House of Lords: Wines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by the Senior Deputy Speaker on 31 July (HL1160), what is the price of the two English wines offered in the House of Lords; and how this compares in each case with the standard House wine on offer.","false","Biography information for Lord Jopling",,"Lord Jopling","HL1380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758377","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>This scheme was procured through a one-off Design and Build contract and Highways England has taken the lessons learnt into all such future schemes to ensure that such difficulties are not replicated.</p><p> </p><p>A pain-gain share mechanism was part of this contract, so the contractor suffered significant losses as a result. Highways England did not issue a ‘Consult Notice’ to the contractor following this scheme, meaning that they did not terminate any forthcoming contracts as a direct result of the contractor’s performance.</p>",,"Lord Callanan",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758377/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T11:36:11.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758377/answer","Biography information for Lord Callanan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758377/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-06","Roads: Construction","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 14 February (HL5245), what steps they have taken to minimise the risk of a repeat escalation of costs by 83 per cent to £13.6 million for the improvements to the A1 road near Gamston Airfield; and what admonishments to individuals or decisions to terminate or decline future contracts with individuals or firms have been taken following the Inquiry which was conducted.","false","Biography information for Lord Jopling",,"Lord Jopling","HL1381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758378","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-18","<p>Speeding fines for motoring offences are directed into the Consolidated Fund. The fund is administered by HM Treasury and is used to support general expenditure on public services such as policing, healthcare, local government grants and transport. Annual accounts for the Fund can be found on the Government’s consolidated fund website.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758378/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-18T11:43:52.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758378/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758378/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-06","Speed Limits: Fines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government where the proceeds from speeding fines for motoring offences are directed; and to what activities and whose budgets they are directed.","false","Biography information for Lord Jopling",,"Lord Jopling","HL1382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758379","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-13","<p>My Department is currently considering reforms to the private parking sector and we are determined to ensure motorists get fair treatment from private parking companies.</p><p>Private parking companies must be a member of a parking trade association if they wish to access DVLA data and issue parking charges. If they do not follow the trade association’s code of practice their access to DVLA data can be suspended.</p><p>We welcome the Rt Hon Sir Greg Knight’s Private Member’s Bill that seeks to create an independent code of practice for private parking companies. We look forward to reading Sir Greg’s recommendations.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758379/answer",,,,,,,,,"2017-09-13T11:56:50.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758379/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/758379/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-06","Parking Offences: Fines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what action they are planning to take against private parking companies that have access to the DVLA database and impose large fines for minor traffic infringements.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1383"
